        <h1>This is a headline for a main module<br/> ITC Lubalin Graph Std 35pt 48px<br/> leading up to 100 bytes.</h1>
        <h2>Debts and complaints against universities should not stop students<br/> graduating or finishing a year, a government watchdog has ruled.</h2>
        <div class="preview-profile clearfix">
            <div class="preview-pic clearfix">
                    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-6 prev-pic">
                        <img src="images/pic.jpg" alt="" />
                        <h3>Adriana Panova 
                        <span>July, 2016</span></h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-6 prev-social">
                        <ul class="social-list">
                            <li class="comments-counts">345<li>
                            <li class="email-icon"><a href="#" title="Email">Email</a></li>
                            <li class="fb-icon"><a href="#" title="Facebook">Facebook</a></li>
                            <li class="twitter-icon"><a href="#" title="Twitter">Twitter</a></li>
                            <li class="whatsapp-icon"><a href="#" title="Whatsapp">Whatsapp</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
            </div>
            <div class="prev-bigimg clearfix">
                <img src="images/img.jpg" alt="" />
            </div>
            <div class="comments-description">
                <p class="firstletter">These and other clauses in contracts between students and their universities were found to be against consumer law after an investigation into higher education terms by the Competition and Markets Authority.</p>
<p>The universites told to change their terms were Birkbeck, University of London, the University of Buckingham and Bucks New University.</p>
<div class="twitter-feeds">
    <h4>Bucks New has agreed not to threaten students with not being able to graduate or progress if they fail to pay rent or library fines to the university.</h4>
    <img src="images/twitter.png" alt="" />
</div>

<p>It was also told to make sure its rules did not put students off complaining.</p>
<p>The university has agreed to withdraw a clause stating: â€˜Where a student is in the process of an informal or formal complaint they may not usually attend a graduation event... Should a student decide to attend a graduation event this will invalidate their complaint.</p>
<p>Birkbeck has agreed to stop allowing for a wide variation in tuition fees within courses and will also ensure students are not deterred from complaining by its procedures.</p>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="preview-btn bottom-btn clearfix">           
            <input type="submit" value="Submit" />
            <input class="back" type="button" value="Back" />
        </div>
    </div>  

